description: There’s a new Batman in town in this issue of Batman Arkham! But does he have what it takes? Meanwhile, in Batman: Arkham Unhinged, the Dark Knight and Catwoman draw in on the Bookbinder, and in Gotham Central, Detective Renee Montoya’s private life comes under scrutiny!

It’s the conclusion to our Arkham Unhinged story this issue, as the Dark Knight closes in on the Bookbinder! But for the new Batman in Detective Comics, he faces his most devious foes yet – La Morte! Meanwhile, in Gotham Central, Montoya’s troubles are just beginning…

Arkham Knight begins here! Yes, this issue of Batman Arkham sees the official debut of the prequel comic to the hit game! You won’t want to miss it! Plus, in Detective Comics, the new Batman faces a mysterious threat, and in Gotham Central, Renee Montoya’s problems are only just beginning!

Welcome to the latest issue of Batman Arkham! In Batman: Arkham Knight, the Caped Crusader faces trouble from the Joker, even after his death! Meanwhile, in Detective Comics, it’s the Joker’s Daughter who’s causing problems! And in Gotham Central, Montoya is in for a nasty surprise! We hope you enjoy all the Batman action!

Batman and Superman find themselves in more peril than ever in this issue of Batman/Superman! In Batman/Superman itself, it may be game over for Batman, but he still fights on! Can Superman help his friend? Meanwhile, in Injustice: Gods Among Us, Superman continues his crusade against criminals at Arkham Asylum. Will the other heroes stand by him? And finally, Superman Unchained sees the Man of Steel teaming up with Wraith against some unstoppable killing machines especially designed to take down Superman!
Linen to Gauze Ch. 1

The first of a two-part epic finale to the first year of the war! Tenebrus unleashes an undead army upon London as the Battle of Britain begins, and Amanda Waller’s Bombshells are united at last. But will even the combined might of Wonder Woman, Supergirl, Batwoman, Stargirl, Aquawoman, Dr. Light and Big Barda be enough to protect a city under siege? Or will one of the Bombshells be called upon to make the ultimate sacrifice?

This issue’s cover joins with the cover to issue #12 to make one big image!
name: The Battle of Britain! Part 1 of 2

description: The seas have extracted a harsh price for Diana’s rescue of the outsider, casting her adrift upon the shores of Man’s World! A kind woman introduces her to this strange new home, and a new friend bolsters her confidence, but throughout the early days of her adventure, strange dreams of violence plague her nights.

In “Claymates,” when Clayface finds himself crumbling and drying up, he seeks a cure by any means necessary! Can Wonder Woman stop him before he enslaves Paradise Island? Then, Diana and Steve go undercover in “Oceans,” where a diplomat crucial to the Panama Canal negotiations has dangerous plans! After a battle with smugglers at home, Wonder Woman is surprised to find a warehouse full of ivory. In Africa, she teams up with the local IADC to track “Orion the Hunter.” Finally, Federal Agent Diana Prince joins a Congressman and his aides to investigate a cult. “Reverend Mike Loves You,” but can you trust his plans for the future?
name: Claymates; Oceans; Orion the Hunter; Reverend Mike Loves You

volume.name: The Return of Lum * Urusei Yatsura Part Two

description: In Batman/Superman itself, Mongul's fatal game continues as heroes clash! Meanwhile, in Injustice: Gods Among Us, War rages in Arkham and one Hero won't survive the assault! And finally, Ascension make a deadly move and all could be lost!

In Batman/Superman, the World’s Finest are set a challenge by Mongul’s successor, and they can’t do it alone! Who will they choose to help them? Meanwhile, in Injustice: Gods Among Us, after the loss of Nightwing, Batman must try and thwart Superman’s plans! And in Superman Unchained, the Man of Steel faces nuclear Armageddon, but what are Wraith’s motives?

Our heroes really have their work cut out for them in this issue! In Batman/Superman, the Superman and Batman Clans face an arena battle to end them all! And in Superman Unchained, the Man of Steel faces the forces of the US Army, while The Dark Knight must fight the powerful Wraith! In Injustice: Gods Among Us, the heroes face further divisions between them, and last but by no means least, this issue sees the debut of Superman, with art by the legendary John Romita Jr.!

We have four amazing stories for you in this issue of Batman Superman! It’s the beginning of a new story, ‘First Contact,’ in Batman/Superman, as the Dark Knight and the Man of Steel team up with Huntress and Power Girl! In Injustice: Gods Among Us, the Insurgency infiltrate the Justice League as the League fight amongst themselves! Meanwhile, in Superman Unchained, Superman battles Wraith, and in Superman, the Man of Steel investigates the mystery surrounding Ulysses!

The Caped Crusader and the Man of Tomorrow team up with Huntress and Power Girl in ‘First Contact,’ while in Injustice: Gods Among Us, the friends are now enemies! In the show-stopping finale to Superman Unchained, Superman faces an alien armada, while in Superman, the Man of Steel and Ulysses come up against the devious Machinist!

The World’s Finest heroes, Superman and Batman are back for another 100 pages of action! See Superman and Batman team up with Power Girl and Huntress! Watch the former friends at odds in Injustice: Gods Among Us! And witness Superman and Ulysses try to defeat the Machinist! Plus, we have the debut of a new strip, Superman Wonder Woman!

It’s another epic issue of Batman Superman! This time, we bring you the conclusion of the ‘First Contact’ crossover, while in Injustice: Gods Among Us, tensions between the Justice League and Insurgency increase! Meanwhile, in Superman Wonder Woman, the power couple investigates Wonderstar, and in Superman, Ulysses surprises the world!

A suburban housewife with a criminal past and a thirst for adrenaline is about to get a top-secret side job: carrying out the government's most dangerous missions.

Renear's husband follows her with the intention of confronting her about a suspected affair. Caught in an act of espionage instead of infidelity, her secret life finally crashes into reality. Is the truth worse than his fears?

Celebrate the birthday of a living legend with an All-New, All-Different, ALL-FREE commemoration of 75 years of Captain America! From fans' first impression of Steve Rogers socking evil in the jaw, to Sam Wilson wielding the shield today, this magazine has it all- bringing you fully up to date with Cap's comics and films! From a guide to the firmest friends and fiercest foes of Cap's storied history, to an in-depth look at his timeless costume, to features focusing on some of the finest creators ever to write or draw the Sentinel of Liberty- including John Romita Sr., Mark Gruenwald, Mark Waid and the King himself, Jack Kirby! Do your patriotic duty and take home this FREE slice of red, white and blue. Happy birthday, Captain- we salute you!

With the Dead Man’s Party winding down, Ghost hunts the mastermind behind the manipulation. But if he’s successful, will it bring Ghost closure and peace? Find out in this action-packed conclusion to the series!

With the life and soul of Scrooge's infant grand nephew hanging on the razor's edge of eternal damnation, the Humbuggers are set for a spectral supernatural showdown against Marley and his malevolent minions. Can Scrooge and our team of paranormal investigators put together lessons from their past, present, and future for one last Christmas miracle? Find out that and more as the mystery of the Fourth Ghost of Christmas is unwrapped and revealed in the blazing and haunting conclusion of 451 Media Group's HUMBUG!!!
A young Buddhist monk must defeat luchador demons and resist the thrall of an enchanted dagger in order to reclaim her own destiny and end a cycle of violence that stretches across lifetimes!

With his father's good name tarnished by a murder accusation, Iron Man heads out west to catch up with Ant-Man! His goal? To find out what REALLY happened to his father in 1940s Hollywood! To find the truth, Iron Man and Ant-Man have to break into an old movie studio that's run by the dangerous SILVERMANE!

It’s the latest issue of Batman Superman, now monthly to celebrate the new movie Batman v Superman: Dawn of Justice! First up, in Batman Superman, Superman journeys into Batman’s brain! Then, in Injustice: Gods Among Us, the Justice League prepares to betray Batman! Plus, in Superman Wonder Woman, the duo takes on Magog! And finally, Superman deals with the fallout of Ulysses’ revelation!
